@startuml fig-connection-vs-session
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Connection (L4) vs session (L5)

participant "Client\napplication" as C #FFE0B2
participant "Server\napplication" as S #C8E6C9

== TCP connection 1 (transport layer) ==

C -> S : SYN / SYN-ACK / ACK
C -> S : HTTP request\n(Cookie: Session-ID=abc)
S --> C : HTTP response (200 OK)
C -> S : FIN

... TCP connection closes ...

== TCP connection 2 (transport layer) ==

C -> S : SYN / SYN-ACK / ACK
C -> S : HTTP request\n(Cookie: Session-ID=abc)
S --> C : HTTP response (200 OK)
C -> S : FIN

note right of S
  Same session "abc" persists
  across two independent
  transport connections.
end note

legend bottom
  A connection is a transport-layer delivery mechanism (L4).
  A session is the logical context of an interaction (L5).
  Sessions can survive connection teardowns and reconnections.
endlegend
@enduml
